@database "blanky"
@author Alfonso Ranieri

@Node "Main" "blanky"

    @{u}@{b}blanky@{ub}@{uu}
    Written by Alfonso Ranieri


    @{" Author " LINK "Author"} @{" WRID " LINK "WRID"} @{" Changes " LINK "Changes"}


    @{fg fill}blanky@{fg text} is a MorphOS DPMS blanker commodity.

    @{fg fill}blanky@{fg text} template and tooltypes are:

    @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY/K/N,CX_POPKEY/K,CX_POPUP/S,METHOD/K,TIMEOUT/K/N@{fg text}

    - @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY@{fg text}
      The priority of the commodity; default: 0

    - @{fg shine}CX_POPKEY@{fg text}
      A key sequence to pop up blanky GUI; default: none

    - @{fg shine}CX_POPUP/S@{fg text}
      If supplied, the GUI is shown

    - @{fg shine}METHOD/K@{fg text}
      Force this method; accepted values are StandBy, Suspend, Off
      Other values are ignored; default: StandBy or your last used prefs

    - @{fg shine}TIMEOUT/K@{fg text}
      Force this timeout; default: 300 (5 mins) or your last used prefs


    You may install @{fg fill}blanky@{fg text} anywhere and run it from WBStartup
    or add the line

    @{fg shine}run >NIL: <NIL: blanky@{fg text}

    to your user-startup.


    The GUI consists of:

    o Options

      - Method
        The method to use to blank your monitor; please, read your monitor manual.

    . StandBy
      Optional state of minimal power reduction

    . Suspend
      Significant reduction of power consumption

    . Off
      Lowest level of power consumption

      - Timeout
        Time of inactivity after which the blanker is activated.

      - Blank key
        Immediate blank keys sequence.

      - Mouse
        If selected, mouse moves stops the blanker.

    o Tasks list

      List of AmigaDOS patterns: if a pattern matches a
      running task, the screen is not blanked.



    blanky opens also an ARexx port name BLANKY on which it
    accepts the following comnands:

    - ACTIVE
      OFF/S
      If OFF is supplied, blanky is not active; also, timeout is not freezed
      If OFF is not supplied, blanky is active; also, timeout is restarted

      It should also be used when setting time, f.e. via utilities like
      NTPSync as in:

       shell "BLANKY" "ACTIVE OFF"
       NTPSync <server>
       shell "BLANKY" "ACTIVE"

      So that "last" is resync with current time

    - HIDE
      -
      Hide blanky GUI

    - QUIT
      FORCE/S
      Same as MUI QUIT ARexx command

    - SHOW
      -
      Show blanky GUI

    - SWITCH
      -
      Switches blanker ON/OFF


@EndNode

@EndNode

